  "text_preview": "\"hair\" ASL American Sign Language ASL University ► hair-dryer HAIRDRYER: Pretend to be holding a \"hairdryer\" in your hand and blow dry your hair. Use a double movement, front to back. Note: I haven't used one of these in a while, but I'm pretty sure this is still the right sign. HAIRDRYER: Animation: Note: The verb form BLOW-DRY is done larger and certainly uses puckered lips as if you were blowing out a birthday cake. See: BLOW-DRY ASL University ► You can learn American Sign Language (ASL) online at American Sign Language University ™ ASL resources by Lifeprint.com © Dr. William Vicars American Sign Language University ™ ASL resources by Lifeprint.com © Dr. William Vicars You can learn American Sign Language (ASL) online at American Sign Language University ™ ASL resources by Lifeprint.c"
